      "Messaging at Scale at Instagram"
     ]
    },
    {
     "cell_type": "markdown",
     "metadata": {},
     "source": [
      "Rick Branson, Infrastructure Engineer"
     ]
    },
    {
     "cell_type": "raw",
     "metadata": {},
     "source": [
      "Async Tasks at Instagram\n",
      "\n",
      "Starts with Feed: See photos by followed friends, time ordered\n",
      "\n",
      "Naive: regular sql call, fetch accounts, photos, sort, limit 10 O(oo)\n",
      "Keys per account \n",
      "\n",
      "Fan-out on write approach - save media id to each account that is followed\n",
      "\n",
      "Has reliability problems\n",
      "\n",
      "Web -> Broker (task queue) -> Workers \n",
      "\n",
      "Chained tasks: small tasks, recursively call to do all followers\n",
      "\n",
      "Async Tasks:\n",
      "- Cross posting to other networking\n",
      "- Search indexing\n",
      "- Span analysis\n",
      "- Account deletion\n",
      "\n",
      "Started with Gearman + Python for queues\n",
      "\n",
      "Replaced with Celery with broker:\n",
      " - Redis (no) limits for memory and task capacity \n",
      " - Beanstalk (no) limit replication\n",
      " - RabbitMQ (yes)\n",
      "\n",
      "Final: Celery (python) + RabbitMQ3 (erlang)\n",
      "\n",
      "Custers of two broker nodes, mirrored\n",
      "scale out by adding clusters\n",
      "EC2 c1.xlarge, RAID instance storage\n",
      "Way overprovisioned\n",
      "\n",
      "Alerting: Sensu (ruby)\n",
      "Monitors on queue length\n",
      "Use `rabbitmqctl list_queues`\n",
      "\n",
      "Graphing: graphite & statsd\n",
      "per-task sent/fail/success\n",
      "\n",
      "Round-robin approach to find broker\n",
      "\n",
      "4000x tasks per second\n",
      "\n",
      "~25000 app threads publishing tasks\n",
      "\n",
      "Celery IRL:\n",
      "- easy to understand and bring up engineers quickly\n",
      "- New job types deployed\n",
      "\n",
      "kombu-multibroker \"shim\" on github\n",
      "https://github.com/rbranson/kombu-multibroker\n",
      "\n",
      "Concurency:\n",
      "- multiprocessing (pre-fork)\n",
      "- gevent\n",
      "- threads (no)\n",
      "\n",
      "celeryd_multi (lots of workers on single box)\n",
      "\n",
      "gevent = Network Bound\n",
      "- facebook api\n",
      "- tumblr api\n",
      "\n",
      "SPlit out tasks between gevent and normal processes\n",
      "\n",
      "Problem: Slow tasks monopolize workers\n",
      "Solution: Separate slow and fast tasks\n",
      "\n",
      "celery config:\n",
      "default: slow task\n",
      "gevent: evented task\n",
      "fast: fast task\n",
      "feed: feed delivery\n",
      "\n",
      "have things move frmo default and promote up to fast via feed\n",
      "\n",
      "Problem: Tasks fail\n",
      "Solution: Celery retry facility (countdown)\n",
      "\n",
      "Problem: Worker crashses lose tasks\n",
      "Solution: ACKS_LATE (ack after worker finishes)\n",
      "\n",
      "1. Get tasks\n",
      "2. Start task\n",
      "3. Ack to broker\n",
      "-- can lose task if worker crashes --\n",
      "4. Worker finishes\n",
      "\n",
      "Why not do all the time?\n",
      "- tasks must be idempotent!\n",
      "- FLP Imposibility\n",
      "\n",
      "No such thing as running tasks just once anyway\n",
      "- FLP Proof\n",
      "- choose to retry or not\n",
      "\n",
      "Problem: Overloaded brokers dropping tasks\n",
      "Solution: Turn on Publisher Confirms mode\n",
      "\n",
      "- AMQP default is we don't know if things published\n",
      "- Publisher Confirms makes broker send acks back on publishes\n",
      "- `kombu-multibroker` forces this\n",
      "- Can cause duplicate tasks (FLP)\n",
      "\n",
      "Avoid using async tasks as a backup mechanism only during failures.  It will break.\n",
      "- Run through queue every time\n",
      "\n",
      "Tasks should execute within a few seconds, any longer its too hard to restart broker\n",
      "\n",
      "SOFT_TIME_LIMIT = 20\n",
      "TIME_LIMIT = 30\n",
      "\n",
      "Future:\n",
      "- Better RabbitMQ Performance\n",
      "- Utilize result storage\n",
      "- Single cluster for control queues\n",
      "- eliminate `kombu-multibroker`"
     ]
    },
